title: Global youth unemployment rate until 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, containing a total of 11 data points.
In general Youth unemployment rate has stayed the same over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2010 and 2011.
Maximum Youth unemployment rate, about 13.2 was reported at Year 2016,  2017,  2018, and 2019
The lowest Youth unemployment rate, of value 12.8 was reported at Year 2011
min_summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Youth unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 11.
Overall Youth unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is roughly constant from 2009 to 2010, slightly decreasing from 2010 to 2011, gradually increasing from 2011 to 2013, roughly constant from 2013 to 2014, gradually increasing from 2014 to 2016, and finally roughly constant from 2016 to 2019.
